    <!-- SAFETY -->
    <h2 id="safety">Important Safety Considerations for Sea Moss + Bladderwrack</h2>

    <div class="warn-box">
      <span class="warn-box-ico">&#9888;</span>
      <p><strong>Iodine caution:</strong> Sea moss and bladderwrack together can provide 200-800mcg of iodine per serving — potentially exceeding the 150mcg RDA significantly. While iodine is essential for thyroid function, excess iodine (above 1,100mcg/day) can suppress thyroid activity. <strong>Do not combine these gummies with separate iodine supplements or kelp products.</strong> If you have any thyroid condition, get your iodine levels tested and consult your endocrinologist before use.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="warn-box">
      <span class="warn-box-ico">&#9888;</span>
      <p><strong>Heavy metal risk:</strong> Seaweeds bioaccumulate minerals from their marine environment, including potential contaminants. Only purchase sea moss products that provide third-party heavy metal testing documentation confirming lead, arsenic, mercury, and cadmium levels below FDA action thresholds. Products without transparent heavy metal testing should be avoided.</p>
    </div>

