    <!-- FAQ -->
    <h2 id="faq">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>What is the sea moss trinity formula?</summary>
      <p>The trinity formula combines sea moss (92 essential minerals), bladderwrack (concentrated iodine for thyroid support), and burdock root (prebiotic fiber and antioxidants). This combination originates from Caribbean herbalism and was popularized by Dr. Sebi as a comprehensive mineral and detoxification protocol.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Does bladderwrack help with thyroid function?</summary>
      <p>Bladderwrack is one of the richest natural iodine sources (200-600mcg/gram). Iodine is essential for T3 and T4 thyroid hormone synthesis. In iodine-deficient individuals, it can support thyroid function. However, iodine content varies widely between batches, and excess iodine can paradoxically suppress thyroid function. Consult an endocrinologist if you have a diagnosed thyroid condition.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>How long does it take for the trinity formula to work?</summary>
      <p>Energy and digestion improvements typically within 2 to 4 weeks. Skin improvements at 4 to 8 weeks. Hair and nail improvements at 3 to 6 months. Maintain consistent daily use for at least 90 days before full evaluation.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Can sea moss gummies replace a multivitamin?</summary>
      <p>Sea moss provides 92 essential minerals but limited vitamin content. It lacks adequate vitamins A, C, D, E, K, and B-complex. Use sea moss as a mineral supplement that complements a balanced diet and, if needed, a multivitamin for the vitamins it does not provide.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>Is sea moss safe with thyroid medication?</summary>
      <p>Sea moss and bladderwrack contain significant iodine that can interact with thyroid medications. Do NOT start without explicit endocrinologist approval if you take levothyroxine, methimazole, or other thyroid medications.</p>
    </details>

    <details class="fq">
      <summary>What is the difference between wildcrafted and pool-grown sea moss?</summary>
      <p>Wildcrafted sea moss is harvested from natural ocean environments with mineral-rich currents, producing higher mineral concentrations. Pool-grown sea moss is cultivated in controlled conditions with potentially lower mineral diversity. Premium brands specify wildcrafted sourcing from the Caribbean or Atlantic coast.</p>
    </details>

